name: icao-standard-atmosphere
description: The International Civil Aviation Organization (ICAO) published their "ICAO Standard Atmosphere" as Doc 7488-CD in 1993. It has the same model as the ISA, but extends the altitude coverage to 80 kilometers (262,500 feet).<sup>[[1](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_Standard_Atmosphere#cite_note-ICAO_1993-7)]</sup>
author: Nathan Witt <wittnl@gmail.com> (http://wi.tt/)
